description: Gets event data results of a query. You must specify the QueryID value returned by the StartQuery operation.

parameters.name: QueryId
parameters.description: The ID of the query for which you want to get results.

nested_items.name: QueryStatus
nested_items.description: The status of the query. Values include QUEUED, RUNNING, FINISHED, FAILED, TIMED_OUT, or CANCELLED.

nested_items.name: QueryStatistics
nested_items.description: Shows the count of query results.

nested_items.name: TotalResultsCount
nested_items.description: The total number of results returned by a query.

nested_items.name: BytesScanned
nested_items.description: The total bytes that the query scanned in the event data store. This value matches the number of bytes for which your account is billed for the query, unless the query is still running.

nested_items.name: QueryResultRows
nested_items.description: Contains the individual event results of the query.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: A token you can use to get the next page of query results.

nested_items.name: ErrorMessage
nested_items.description: The error message returned if a query failed.
